result.execSummary:
The defendant Colin D. Gile was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Pay court costs and Department of Corrections Supervision Fees. Payment is due within 30 days.  If the Defendant cannot make the payment, he/she must report to the Clerk of Courts Office to set up a payment plan.  Failure to comply will result in other collection methods including a civil Judgment and/or suspension of your drivers license for one (1) year.  This judgment may be collected by income assignment if you fail to pay fines and costs as ordered.
COC COLLECT 
-------------------

No violent contact with the victim. No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. No alcohol. Not to operate a motor vehicle without a valid license.
-------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent. Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge. 
-------------------
AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief

Defendant Colin D. Gile in court.  Attorney Keith Kolby Venema in court for Colin D. Gile.  Prosecuting attorney Vivien L. TenHaken in court for the State of Wisconsin. Victim also present in court. Parties have reached an agreement. Defendant plead guilty to Count #1. Plea questionnaire/waiver of rights filed. Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges defendant guilty. Defendant does not make statement. Court gives warning to deportation. Court sentences defendant. Minutes filed.
Signed bond filed with the court.

BOND TO COVER 22CM384, 22CM216, 22CM26

*AMENDMENT 6-9-22: NO VIOLENT CONTACT WITH D.M.C. "No violent contact" includes threats through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person or through a third party. 

DEFENDANT MUST POST $500 CASH (ALREADY POSTED)

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol.  Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons.  Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH D.M.C OR HER RESIDENCE.  If defendant and victim(s) are living together, defendant may go to their residence once with a police officer to retrieve the defendant's personal belongings.  Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.

Prosecuting attorney James T. Sempf in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Colin D. Gile in court. Attorney Keith Venema for defendant. Motion to modify bond by State, argument, bond remains. Defendant given complaint; charges/penalties explained by the court. Not guilty plea entered by counsel and trial reserved. Minutes filed.
Status conference scheduled for August 31, 2022 at 08:30 am.
